import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["delay"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["distance"].median():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False).head(10)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="counts", y="origin", hue="destination", data=data, dodge=False)
    ax.set(xlabel='Number of Flights', ylabel='Origin Airport')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the most flights?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
